        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 3:57PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ridge Spring, or 8 miles southwest of Batesburg-Leesville, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Batesburg-Leesville, Ridge Spring, Pelion, Gilbert, Summit, Monetta,
Ward, Cedar Grove Fire Station, South Shore Marina, Oswald Park,
Fredonia, Murray, Camp Kinard, Delmar, Hollow Creek Public Park,
Hibernia, Steedman, Kneece, Samaria Fire Station, and Cedar Pond
Campground.

This includes Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 22
and 50.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
